title: For Sale:  AR-15 Piston Kit - Osprey 416 and Midwest Quad Rail
postcontent:
I have a used Osprey 416 Piston kit that has less than 100 rounds use on it.  I bought it back at the beginning of the scare but sold the gun it was installed in, and so am selling the kit seperately.  The kit works GREAT and is quite easy to install assuming you have basic AR skills.  This is the carbine length kit and will only work with carbine length gas systems.  It includes everything found in the original kit, except that it has a couple of additional pins that I requested from Osprey when I bought it in case one were to get lost.

Here is a link to the kit with description: http://www.midwayusa.com/product/915714/osprey-defense-ops-416-gas-piston-retrofit-conversion-kit-ar-15-standard-barrel-diameter-carbine-length 

I also have the Carbine length Midwest 2 Piece Free Float Quad-Rail that was designed to work with this system.  It is also very easy to install, though you do have to remove the delta pack from your AR (the standard barrel nut remains), but you have to take off the spring, c-clip, and delta ring.  You can either remove the barrel with a barrel wrench to do it, or just cut the ring off with a dremel if you don't want to break the gun down.  The rail is rock-solid.  It is a very nice piece.  It does have a couple of small scratches on it, but nothing major.  It just got bumped around in the safe.  

Here is a link to the rail:  http://www.midwayusa.com/product/178594/midwest-industries-gas-piston-free-float-tube-handguard-quad-rail-ar-15-carbine-length-aluminum-black

As you can see, these parts new run over $500.

title: For Sale:  Heavy .44 Magnum Ammo - 305 gr. L.B.T.-L.F.N. (1,325 fps/M.E. 1,189 ft. lbs.) - 20 Round Box - Big Game up to 1000 lbs.
postcontent:
http://extreme-impact-ammo.com/index.php?l=product_detail&p=49

Item 4A (305gr. Hard Cast gas Checked LFN) is designed for super deep penetration on large game. The big flat nose keeps the bullet penetrating straight and thus deep. You can expect a good three + feet of penetration in normal flesh and bone. The flat nose also does considerably more damage than a round nosed type of bullet as the flat nose cuts and smashes it way through living matter, while round nosed bullets tend to slip and slide through matter, doing much less damage along the bullet’s path and achieving more shallow penetration due to getting sideways while “slipping and sliding” through matter.

Item 4A is recommended for all STEEL revolvers and rifles on today’s market. It is not suitable for scandium or aluminum alloy revolvers.

The gun has been duracoated and is covered completely in a tactical woodland tan/coyote tan mix, and the bolt is just woodland tan. Besides the rifling this gun is completely rust proof. I have gotten .25 moa groups out of this gun with handloads but with cheap factory ammo its still under 1 moa. The base on it is a 20 moa rail. There also is a aftermarket hogue grip on the chassis.

6"x6"x40", pure 304 Stainless Steel. Tank, cover, and Stainless Steel ball valve are included. 

We are proud to offer the very best Parkerizing Tanks in the industry. They are cut and formed out of pure 304 stainless steel. Handles are formed right into the ends. All edges of these tanks are hemmed, so there are no exposed sharp edges. Feel free to handle these tank with your bare hands!

title: For Sale:  Rice Bran Pellets
location: Ft. Smith and surrounding cities, Fort Smith, AR, Oklahoma
postcontent:
RICE BRAN PELLETS
• Does your horse have trouble keeping weight on?
• Do you want to add more healthy calories to his diet?
• Do you want to help your horse build lean muscle?
•	Do you want to draw the deer to your feeder and deer stand?
•	Do you want to see huge racks on your bucks?

If you answered "YES" to any of these questions, a rice bran supplement may be just what you need...it can provide all these benefits and more.

Rice bran (RB) can be a great addition to many horses, all livestock and wildlife’s diets.  But what is it?  When the rice seed is harvested, there are three stages.  The first stage takes off the hull to make brown rice.  Then the second stage removes the brown layer to make white rice. It is this brown layer that is the bran.

The high fat content makes it an ideal choice to feed to performance horses, broodmares and weanlings, older horses, all livestock and wildlife that need additional calories in their diet to maintain performance or increase body weight.  Weighing in at almost 20% oil, RB has a very high fat content.

RB weighs in at approximately 1200 calories per pound, making it a very effective weight building feed.  It is not as high in calories as oil (4000 calories/pound) because oil is 100% fat while RB contains other things such as fiber, some starch, calcium, phosphorous and protein.
Benefits of feeding

Not only is RB a highly palatable fat source, it also has a few other benefits: It contains gamma oryzanol.  Gamma oryzanol is thought to help muscle repair and rebuilding.  Many horse owners have reported increased lean muscle mass in horses that are on RB.  Rice bran is a rich natural source of vitamin E and gamma-oryzanol, which have been extensively studied and reported to possess important health-promoting properties.  Deer hunters have reported bigger body mass and racks.

It has a significant amount of fiber in addition to the fat.  The fiber in the RB makes it less likely to cause digestive upset than other calorie sources that contain large amounts of starch.  Studies have shown feeding rice bran greatly reduces colic, stomach ulcers and other digestive problems associated with grains.  Due to its mixed composition, RB is an ideal fat source for many horses, livestock and wildlife.  

For more information please call or text REDACTED 
$12.50 per bag.  Bag weight 60 lbs.

Our rice bran pellets have been analyzed by a certified lab for its nutritional value. 

Dr. David Freeman, Animal Nutritionist, Oklahoma State University says this about our rice bran:  “Shows to be a very sound feed, protein similar to corn, fat higher than oats or corn, calcium higher than phosphorus.  All suggest a very adequate feed for most broodmares, weanlings, performance and older horses or any livestock and wildlife.”
